    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="556"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.24/8–1944</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 17461</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-19">August 19,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received August 24.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my despatch No. 16875 of July
                        13<note n="6" xml:id="d556fn6">See footnote 2, <ref target="#pg_586">p.
                            586</ref>.</note> concerning the disposition of certain construction
                    equipment to the Brazilian Government, I have the honor to enclose copy and
                    translation of a communication from the Minister of Transportation and Public
                    Works, General Mendonça Lima,<note n="6a" xml:id="d556fn6a">Not printed.</note>
                    stating that the new proposal, as Set out in my letter to him of July 13, a copy
                    of which was forwarded to the Department annexed to my despatch under reference,
                    has been entirely accepted by President Vargas and that funds will be made
                    available to take care of the expenses involved in accordance with the terms of
                    our proposal. I have informed General Wooten of this. It would be appreciated if
                    this information could be transmitted to the War Department.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
